{"hierarchy":{"paths":[],"reference":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/BuildingSyncUps"},"sections":[{"action":{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Get started","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/WhatIsSyncUps","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Get started","type":"text"}]},"title":"Building SyncUps","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The SyncUps application is a recreation of one of Apple’s more interesting demo applications,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Scrumdinger. We recreate it from scratch using the Composable Architecture, with a focus on"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"domain modeling, controlling dependencies, and testability."}]}],"kind":"hero"},{"content":[],"name":null,"kind":"volume","chapters":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Let’s start with a tour of the application we will be building. It’s called SyncUps, and it’s a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"recreation of the Apple’s Scrumdinger demo application."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"image":"chapter1.png","name":"What is SyncUps?","tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/WhatIsSyncUps"]},{"name":"Lists of sync-ups","image":"chapter2.png","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"We will begin building the SyncUps app from scratch by implementing the feature that powers the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"list of sync-ups. It starts out as a simple feature, but it will become increasingly complex as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the app evolves."}]}],"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ListsOfSyncUps","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingListOfSyncUps"]},{"image":"chapter3.png","tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpForm","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpForm"],"name":"New sync-up form","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Let’s build a new feature for editing the details of a sync-up in a form. This will allow us to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"explore the binding tools the library provides, and we will add some complex logic around focus","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in the form, and show how it is 100% testable."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"We now have two features built, the sync-ups list and the sync-up form. These features do not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"exist in isolation, but rather are meant to be integrated in a deep way. One should be able to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"navigate to the sync-up form from the list view, enter the details of a new sync-up, and then"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"add that sync-up to the root list.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Presenting the sync-up form","image":"chapter4.png","tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentingSyncUpForm","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpFormPresentation"]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Applications typically need to persist data across application launches. The Composable","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Architecture comes with tools to help you persist your application’s data."}]}],"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/PersistingSyncUps"],"image":"chapter5.png","name":"Persisting sync-ups to disk"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The next feature to build is the “detail” screen for a sync-up. This feature allows the user to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"edit a sync-up, record a new meeting, see past recorded meetings, and even delete the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"sync-up.","type":"text"}]}],"image":"chapter6.png","name":"Sync-up detail","tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpDetail","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/EditingAndDeletingSyncUp","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpDetail"]},{"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpDetailNavigation","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/MeetingNavigation","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingNavigation"],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We now have a sync-up detail screen, but still no way to navigate to it from the rest of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"app. We want to be able to drill-down to the detail screen from the list screen."}]}],"name":"Navigating to sync-up detail","image":"chapter7.png"},{"name":"Record meeting","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The app is almost complete! But we have saved the most difficult feature for last: recording"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a new meeting. This requires interfacing with two complex dependencies, a speech recognizer","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and timer, and requires some subtle behavior that we are definitely going to want to get","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"test coverage on."}]}],"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/RecordMeetingFeature","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ImplementingTimer","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ImplementingSpeechRecognizer"],"image":"chapter8.png"}],"image":null}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"kind":"overview","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/tutorials\/buildingsyncups"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/BuildingSyncUps","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"category":"Building SyncUps","estimatedTime":"3hr 10min","categoryPathComponent":"BuildingSyncUps","role":"overview","title":"Building SyncUps"},"references":{"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/BuildingSyncUps":{"type":"topic","title":"Building SyncUps","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/BuildingSyncUps","role":"overview","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The SyncUps application is a recreation of one of Apple’s more interesting demo applications,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Scrumdinger. We recreate it from scratch using the Composable Architecture, with a focus on","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"domain modeling, controlling dependencies, and testability."}],"url":"\/tutorials\/buildingsyncups","kind":"overview"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/PersistingSyncUps":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/PersistingSyncUps","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Now that we have the ability to add and remove sync-ups from the application, let’s add some","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"persistence. This will involve using the “shared state” tools from the library, such as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"@Shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fileStorage"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"kind":"project","role":"project","title":"Persisting sync-ups","estimatedTime":"5min","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/persistingsyncups"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/SyncUpDetail":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpDetail","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The “sync-up detail” screen shows all the information of a sync-up, and has many actions that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"can take place in the screen. The user can edit the sync-up, or start a new meeting in the sync"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"up, or drill-down to a past meeting, or even delete the meeting."}],"kind":"project","role":"project","title":"Sync-up detail","estimatedTime":"5min","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/syncupdetail"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/TestingNavigation":{"type":"topic","title":"Testing navigation","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingNavigation","role":"project","abstract":[{"text":"We have now implemented a navigation stack at the root of our application, and integrated","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"3 features into the stack: the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SyncUpsList"},{"type":"text","text":" feature, the "},{"code":"SyncUpDetail","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" feature, and the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"MeetingView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Some of these features have quite complex logic binding them together, such as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when one deletes a sync-up from the detail screen it should pop the screen off the stack."}],"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/testingnavigation","kind":"project","estimatedTime":"10min"},"chapter3.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter3.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","identifier":"chapter3.png","alt":null},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/ImplementingSpeechRecognizer":{"type":"topic","title":"Adding a speech recognizer","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ImplementingSpeechRecognizer","role":"project","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We have just one feature left to implement, and it’s one of the most complicated ones. We need"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to use Apple’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"SFSpeechRecognizer","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" API to ask the user for permission to transcribe their"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"audio, and then start a speech recognition task to live transcribe the meeting while it is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in progress."}],"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/implementingspeechrecognizer","kind":"project","estimatedTime":"10min"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/ImplementingTimer":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ImplementingTimer","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The first major piece of logic and behavior we will introduce to the record meeting feature is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the timer. This is a long-living effect that runs in parallel with the rest of the feature, and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"we need to implement nuanced logic to figure out when to proceed to the next speaker."}],"kind":"project","role":"project","title":"Adding a meeting timer","estimatedTime":"25min","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/implementingtimer"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/PresentingSyncUpForm":{"type":"topic","title":"Presenting the sync-up form","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentingSyncUpForm","role":"project","abstract":[{"text":"We now have two features built: the sync-ups list and the sync-up form. These features do not","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"exist in isolation, but rather are meant to be integrated in a deep way. One should be able to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"navigate to the sync-up form from the list view, enter the details of a new sync-up, and then"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"add that sync-up to the root list."}],"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/presentingsyncupform","kind":"project","estimatedTime":"10min"},"chapter5.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter5.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","identifier":"chapter5.png","alt":null},"chapter4.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter4.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","identifier":"chapter4.png","alt":null},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/TestingSyncUpDetail":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpDetail","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"SyncUpDetail","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" feature has slowly become quite complex. It now handles two forms of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"navigation (an alert and sheet), it models navigation state with a single enum, and it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"updates the parent feature via a shared property. It’s about time we got some test"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"coverage on this feature so we can be sure it works as we expect, and so that we can make future"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"changes with confidence."}],"kind":"project","role":"project","title":"Testing the sync-up detail","estimatedTime":"10min","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/testingsyncupdetail"},"chapter1.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter1.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","identifier":"chapter1.png","alt":null},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/SyncUpForm":{"type":"topic","title":"Sync-up form","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpForm","role":"project","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We will create a new feature with the Composable Architecture that is capable of editing the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"details of a new sync-up. We will also add some nuanced logic around how focus moves through the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"feature to make things a little more interesting.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/syncupform","kind":"project","estimatedTime":"15min"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/ListsOfSyncUps":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ListsOfSyncUps","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"We will begin building the SyncUps app from scratch by implementing the feature that powers the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"list of sync-ups. It starts out as a simple feature, but it will become increasingly complex as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the app evolves."}],"kind":"project","role":"project","title":"Lists of sync-ups","estimatedTime":"10min","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/listsofsyncups"},"chapter8.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter8.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","identifier":"chapter8.png","alt":null},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/MeetingNavigation":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/MeetingNavigation","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Now that we have a navigation stack in place we can start navigating to other features in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"application. The simplest is the meeting screen, which allows you to see the details of a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"previous recorded meeting."}],"kind":"project","role":"project","title":"Navigating to a meeting","estimatedTime":"5min","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/meetingnavigation"},"chapter2.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter2.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","identifier":"chapter2.png","alt":null},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/TestingSyncUpFormPresentation":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpFormPresentation","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"We have now integrated two moderately complex features, the ","type":"text"},{"code":"SyncUpsList","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SyncUpForm"},{"type":"text","text":", and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"so its time to write some tests. This will give us the opportunity to prove that the features"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"work in tandem as we expect, and we will explore “non-exhaustive” testing to make our tests less","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"fragile."}],"kind":"project","role":"project","title":"Testing the add sync-up flow","estimatedTime":"10min","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/testingsyncupformpresentation"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/RecordMeetingFeature":{"type":"topic","title":"The RecordMeeting feature","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/RecordMeetingFeature","role":"project","abstract":[{"text":"Let’s get the basics of a new feature into place that we can navigate to, and then we will","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"slowly layer on its complex logic and behavior, such as the timer and speech recognizer."}],"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/recordmeetingfeature","kind":"project","estimatedTime":"5min"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/EditingAndDeletingSyncUp":{"type":"topic","title":"Editing and deleting a sync-up","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/EditingAndDeletingSyncUp","role":"project","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s implement two major pieces of functionality in the detail screen: editing the sync-up and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"deleting the sync-up. This will force us to face a number of common problems in app development"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"all at once, including view reuse, navigation, alerts, and parent-child communication patterns."}],"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/editinganddeletingsyncup","kind":"project","estimatedTime":"30min"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/TestingListOfSyncUps":{"type":"topic","title":"Testing the list of sync-ups","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingListOfSyncUps","role":"project","abstract":[{"text":"The SyncUpsList feature we have built so far isn’t very complex. In fact, it only has one","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"primary action, that of deleting sync-ups from its collection. However, it can be good practice","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to test new features as you add them, and in the future we will have much more complicated"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"behavior to test.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/testinglistofsyncups","kind":"project","estimatedTime":"5min"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/TestingSyncUpForm":{"type":"topic","title":"Testing the sync-up form","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpForm","role":"project","abstract":[{"text":"We now have a moderately complex feature for editing the details of a sync-up, the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SyncUpForm"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"reducer. Let’s get some test coverage on the feature, and doing so will force us to come","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"face-to-face with dependencies for the first time in this tutorial.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/testingsyncupform","kind":"project","estimatedTime":"10min"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/SyncUpDetailNavigation":{"type":"topic","title":"Navigating to a sync-up detail","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpDetailNavigation","role":"project","abstract":[{"text":"We will wrap the application built so far in a ","type":"text"},{"code":"NavigationStack","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" so that we can navigate to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the detail screen. To do this we will create a new root-level feature that will be responsible"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for implementing the logic of the stack and integrating all of the features together."}],"url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/syncupdetailnavigation","kind":"project","estimatedTime":"20min"},"chapter7.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter7.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","identifier":"chapter7.png","alt":null},"chapter6.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter6.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","identifier":"chapter6.png","alt":null},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/WhatIsSyncUps":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/WhatIsSyncUps","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s start with a tour of the application we will be building. It’s called SyncUps, and it’s a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"recreation of Apple’s Scrumdinger demo application.","type":"text"}],"kind":"project","role":"project","title":"What is SyncUps?","estimatedTime":"5min","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/whatissyncups"}}}